    <description>I saw [this post](https://githyankidiaspora.com/2021/01/31/planescape-tables-for-the-outlands/) by the well-known blogger, podcaster and RPG great  **Judd Karlman** .

It got me thinking about random table structures, and so I wrote this:

![fgtrtdcover- (1)|357x500](upload://coHcglEvVomGsfreab4C9yHvuZ1.png) 

Link to PDF: [https://www.drivethrurpg.com/product/398839/Field-Guide-to-Random-Table-Design-in-RPGs](https://www.drivethrurpg.com/product/398839/Field-Guide-to-Random-Table-Design-in-RPGs)

The idea here is to consider how to make/tweak random table structures to suit your RPG needs.

It probably overeggs the pudding. However, if this might be of interest, please check it out.

:O)</description>
    
